Visitors view the exhibition Photo: Courtesy of Yu Yang   
A new exhibition at the Cheng Center for Contemporary Art in Beijing's 798 Art Zone is exhibited various works young artist Li Jing has created over the past three years. Repeat explores the artist's painting series like Palette and Mensonge as well as the installation Travel Through. According to the artist, Repeat does not just represent her approach to creating art, but also stands for her personal style of thinking about and exploring the world. Han Yali, the artistic director of the Cheng Center for Contemporary Art, said that this first exhibition of 2022 took six months of preparation and that they chose Li to give more opportunities to young artists. The exhibition is set to run until Sunday.